items.name: TensorWorks
items.description: A versatile tensor library designed for efficient machine learning operations. This library provides robust tools for tensor manipulation, enabling seamless integration with various machine learning frameworks. Ideal for researchers and developers aiming to optimize their machine learning workflows.

items.name: Object-Detection
items.description: This project aims to develop a real-time object detection system using Python and popular deep learning frameworks. Object detection is a crucial task in computer vision, enabling machines to identify and locate objects within images or video streams.

items.name: Hybrid-ML-DL_Nanofluid-Density-Predictor
items.description: This repository contains code for a comprehensive hybrid machine learning and deep learning frameworks for accurately predicting hybrid nanofluid density using stacking ensembles, advanced data augmentation, and metaheuristic optimization techniques.

items.name: Nanofluid-Thermophysical-Property-Prediction_Thermal-Conductivity_Hybrid-ML-DL
items.description: This repository contains code for a comprehensive hybrid machine learning and deep learning frameworks for accurately predicting nanofluid thermal conductivity using stacking ensembles, advanced data augmentation, and metaheuristic optimization techniques.

items.name: Advanced-Nanofluid-Heat-Capacity-Prediction_Hybrid-ML-DL
items.description: This repository contains code for a comprehensive hybrid machine learning and deep learning frameworks for accurately predicting nanofluid specific heat capacity using stacking ensembles, advanced data augmentation, and metaheuristic optimization techniques.

items.name: QuantTradeAI
items.description: A comprehensive machine learning framework for quantitative trading strategies

items.name: video2x
items.description: A machine learning-based video super resolution and frame interpolation framework. Est. Hack the Valley II, 2018.

items.name: sagemaker-distribution
items.description: A set of Docker images that include popular frameworks for machine learning, data science and visualization.

items.name: wildlife-collision-prediction
items.description: Machine learning framework for predicting wildlife-vehicle collisions using environmental features extracted from satellite imagery and road segment data. Integrates Landsat imagery analysis with spatial data processing to identify high-risk road segments

items.name: XAI_framework
items.description: The XAI Framework API is a Flask-based machine learning model deployment that allows users to:  Make predictions using a trained model (/predict) Get model explanations using LIME (/explain/lime)

items.name: ML-LITE
items.description: ML-LITE is a C++ machine learning framework featuring models built from scratch, designed for exploration, learning, and reusability.

items.description: An Open-Source Machine Learning Framework in Rust Œî

items.description: A machine learning framework in Zig and OpenCL.

items.name: Cortex
items.description: Basic machine learning framework made in C

items.name: StreamlitApp
items.description: Streamlit is an open-source app framework primarily used for building interactive, data-driven web applications in Python. It is especially popular for its simplicity and ease of use, allowing you to create web apps with just a few lines of code. You can use it to visualize data, deploy machine learning models, or even create dashboards.

items.name: agent-framework
items.description: EchoAI is a next-generation AI-powered trading solution that leverages decentralized intelligence for automated, high-efficiency market strategies. Designed to optimize financial decision-making, EchoAI combines cutting-edge machine learning with blockchain security to enhance trading precision and adaptability.

items.name: anacostia-pipeline
items.description: Anacostia is a framework for creating machine learning operations (MLOps) pipelines

items.name: OpenPyStruct
items.description: Open-source toolkit that provides finite element model based optimization frameworks for generating training data and machine learning models for global structural optimization of indeterminate continuous structures

items.name: GelGenie
items.description: Open-Source package for segmentation and analysis of gel electrophoresis images using machine learning.  Both a python framework for training/running models and a QuPath GUI extension are available.

items.name: media-insights-on-aws
items.description: A serverless framework to accelerate the development of applications that discover next-generation insights in your video, audio, text, and image resources by utilizing AWS Machine Learning and Media services.

items.name: Course_Recommender_System
items.description: The Course Recommendation System is a final project of the IBM Machine Learning Specialization implemented using Python and streamlit framework, offering an interactive web application for personalized course recommendations

Built using Python, Django frameworks and machine learning algorithms like XGBoost and  Random Forest.
